Package de.wwu.muggl.symbolic.flow.defUseChains.structures

Provides axuiliary classes for representing def-use chains and their constituting elements.

See:
          Description

Interface Summary
DefUseVariable There are several kinds of variables than can form def-use chains.
 

Class Summary
AbstractObjectAttribute This abstract DefUseVariable represents a field of an object being accessed by a method.
Def This class represents a definition of a variable.
LocalVariable This DefUseVariable represents a local variable of a method.
ObjectAttribute This DefUseVariable represents a field of an object being accessed by a method.
ObjectAttributeCandidate This DefUseVariable represents a possible access of a field of an object.
StackPosition This DefUseVariable represents a position on the operand stack of a method.
StaticAttribute This DefUseVariable represents a static field being accessed by a method.
Use This class represents an usage of a variable.
 

Package de.wwu.muggl.symbolic.flow.defUseChains.structures Description

Provides axuiliary classes for representing def-use chains and their constituting elements.
